description: From Yagara bunya bunya; compare also Waka-Kabic forms such as Gabi bunyi, Wakawaka bunyi.

entries.meaning: The bunya pine, Araucaria bidwillii, native to Queensland. [from 19th c.]
examples: Her three favourite bunyah-bunyah nut trees were destroyed last year to make way for more grazing land for sheep and other animals whose cloven hooves destroyed the delicate topsoil and laid bare the earth.

entries.meaning: (dated, India) A banyan, a member of a specific Hindu caste.
